Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Linear Algebraic Methods): The paper deals with linear programming feasibility problem and linear optimization over the solution set, which are typical topics in this sub-category.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper introduces an algorithm for solving a new class of semilinear CSPs in polynomial time, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper mentions the study of semilinear relations in connection with algebraic geometry, which is a topic in this sub-category.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper deals with constraint satisfaction problems and the existence of integer solutions, which are typical topics in this sub-category.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper fully determines the complexity for all finite sets of semilinear relations containing R+, which is a topic in this sub-category.
